article.headline: SE Missouri 88, E. Kentucky 74
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Roderick Pearson scored 22 points as Southeast Missouri State rallied for an 88-74 win over Eastern Kentucky on Tuesday night. The Redhawks (4-11, 2-4 Ohio Valley Conference) trailed 43-32 early in the second half but used an 8-0 run to take the lead for good at 57-51 with 10 minutes left in the game. Eastern (8-5, 3-2) narrowed the margin to 59-57 with 8:26 left, but SEMO put the game away with an 18-2 run, making the score 77-59 with 2:50 remaining. Southeast Missouri made 13 shots from 3-point range, compared with 10 for the hosts. Pearson scored 14 points in the second half and had 11 assists. Brandon Foust, Terrick Willoughby and David Johnson had 14 points each for the Redhawks. Adam Leonard led the Colonels with 17 points, Josh Daniel followed with 15, scoring 12 in the first half. Mike Rose added 14, Julian Mascoll 12 and Darnell Dialls 10. Eastern trailed 28-24 with seven minutes remaining in the first half but closed the period with a 17-4 run for a 41-32 halftime lead. Daniel scored five points during the spurt, all in back-to-back fashion.
